{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"name":"ir","display_name":"R","language":"R"},"language_info":{"name":"R","codemirror_mode":"r","pygments_lexer":"r","mimetype":"text/x-r-source","file_extension":".r","version":"4.0.5"}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"source":"<a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/code/davitghazaryan/cyclistic-2023-01-2023-07-analysis?scriptVersionId=144671668\" target=\"_blank\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"Kaggle\" title=\"Open in Kaggle\" src=\"https://kaggle.com/static/images/open-in-kaggle.svg\"></a>","metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown"},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Introduction**\n\nThis is my Google Data Analytics Professional Certificate course's capstone project. I'll be using the R programming language and RStudio for the analysis because of their simple statistical analysis tools and data visualizations.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**The steps for data analysis for this project are as follows:**\n    \n   **ASK                                                                                                       \n   Prepare                                                                                             \n   Process                                                                                                        \n   Analyze                                                                                                       \n   Share                                                                                                              \n   Act**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Scenario**\n\nYou are a junior data analyst working in the marketing analyst team at Cyclistic, a bike-share company in Chicago. The director of marketing believes the company’s future success depends on maximizing the number of annual memberships. Therefore, your team wants to understand how casual riders and annual members use Cyclistic bikes differently. From these insights, your team will design a new marketing strategy to convert casual riders into annual members. But first, Cyclistic executives must approve your recommendations, so they must be backed up with compelling data insights and professional data visualizations.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Ask**\n\nThree questions will guide the future marketing program:\n\n1.How do annual members and casual riders use Cyclistic bikes differently?                                              \n2.Why would casual riders buy Cyclistic annual memberships?                                           \n3.How can Cyclistic use digital media to influence casual riders to become members?\n\n**Key tasks**\n \n **1.Identify the business task**                                                                                     \n     The main objective is to build the best marketing strategies to turn casual bike riders into annual members by analyzing        how the 'Casual' and 'Annual' customers use Cyclistic bike share differently.                         \n **2.Consider key stakeholders**                                                                                          \n     Cyclistic executive team, Director of Marketing (Lily Moreno), Marketing Analytics team.                       \n**Deliverable**                          \n   **A clear statement of the business task**                                                  \n     Find the differences between casual and member riders.  ","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Prepare**                                                                                                       \n  I will use Cyclistic’s historical trip data to analyze and identify trends. The data has been made available by **Motivate     International Inc.** under this license. Datasets are avilable here.                 \n**Key tasks**\n \n  **Download data and store it appropriately.**\n  \n   Data has been downloaded from [here](https://divvy-tripdata.s3.amazonaws.com/index.html) and copies have been stored securely on my computer and here on Kaggle.\n    \n  **Identify how it’s organized.**\n   \n   All trip data is in comma-delimited (.CSV) format. Column names \"ride_id\", \"rideable_type\", \"started_at\", \"ended_at\",          \"start_station_name\", \"start_station_id\", \"end_station_name\", \"end_station_id\", \"start_lat\", \"start_lng\", \"end_lat\",            \"end_lng\", \"member_casual\" (Total 13 column)   \n   \n  **Sort and filter the data.**\n   \n   For this analysis I'm going to use from Jan up until Jun for 7 months data of the year 2023, as it's last current data we have for 2023.\n\n  **Determine the credibility of the data.**\n\n   For the purposes of this case study, the datasets are appropriate and it will enable me to answer the business questions.      But due data-privacy I cannot use rider's personally identification information, and this will prevent me from determining      if a single user/rider taken several rides. All ride ids are unique in this data-set.  \n   \n  **Deliverable**                                                                                                     \n    A description of all data sources used                                                                         \n     Main source of data provided by the [Cylistic company.](https://divvy-tripdata.s3.amazonaws.com/index.html)","metadata":{"_kg_hide-input":false}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## install and load necessary packages\nlibrary(tidyverse)\nlibrary(ggplot2)\nlibrary(lubridate)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:08.897547Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:08.900222Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:08.925462Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## imprt data in R studio\njan23<-read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/cicllistic-bike-share-2023/202301-divvy-tripdata/202301-divvy-tripdata.csv\")\nfeb23<-read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/cicllistic-bike-share-2023/202302-divvy-tripdata/202302-divvy-tripdata.csv\")\nmar23<-read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/cicllistic-bike-share-2023/202303-divvy-tripdata/202303-divvy-tripdata.csv\")\napr23<-read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/cicllistic-bike-share-2023/202304-divvy-tripdata/202304-divvy-tripdata.csv\")\nmay23<-read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/cicllistic-bike-share-2023/202305-divvy-tripdata/202305-divvy-tripdata.csv\")\njun23<-read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/cicllistic-bike-share-2023/202306-divvy-tripdata/202306-divvy-tripdata.csv\")\njul23<-read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/cicllistic-bike-share-2023/202307-divvy-tripdata/202307-divvy-tripdata.csv\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:08.929352Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:08.931277Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:19.078322Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## checking data sets for consistency\ncolnames(jan23)\ncolnames(feb23)\ncolnames(mar23)\ncolnames(apr23)\ncolnames(may23)\ncolnames(jun23) \ncolnames(jul23)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:19.082409Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:19.083914Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:19.137614Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## check data structures (dbl,chr,date)\nstr(jan23)\nstr(feb23)\nstr(mar23)\nstr(apr23)\nstr(may23)\nstr(jun23)  \nstr(jul23)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:19.141517Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:19.143276Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:19.375163Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## merge all monts data frame into one large data frame\ntrips23<-bind_rows(jan23, feb23, mar23, apr23, may23, jun23, jul23)\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:19.379019Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:19.380429Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:21.308257Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":" **Process**                                                                                 \n     Cleaning and Preparation of data for analysis\n\n **Key tasks**                                                                                        \n     Check the data for errors.                                                                             \n     Choose your tools.                                                                                \n     Transform the data so you can work with it effectively.                                                              \n     Document the cleaning process.                                                                              \n **Deliverable**                                                                                          \n     Documentation of any cleaning or manipulation of data                                                               \n                                                                                     \n**Following code chunks will be used for this 'Process' phase.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## checking merged data frame\ncolnames(trips23)   ## List of column names\nhead(trips23)       ## See the first 6 rows of data frame.  Also tail(tripdata)\nstr(trips23)        ## See list of columns and data types (numeric, character, etc)\nsummary(trips23)    ## Statistical summary of data. Mainly for numeric.","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:21.310943Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:21.312226Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:22.931674Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**CLEAN UP AND ADD DATA TO PREPARE FOR ANALYSIS**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## Removing ride_id,start_station_name,start_station_id,end_station_name,end_station_id,start_lat,start_lng,end_lat,end_lng \n##  as we are not using for now \ntrips23<-trips23 %>%\nselect(-c(ride_id,start_station_name,start_station_id,end_station_name,end_station_id,start_lat,start_lng,end_lat,end_lng ))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:22.934303Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:22.935682Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:22.95535Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## Inspectind the new table that has been created\ncolnames(trips23)  ## List of column names\nnrow(trips23)      ## How many rows are in data frame?\ndim(trips23)       ## Dimendions of the data frame ?\nhead(trips23)      ## See the first 6 rows of data frame.  Also tail(tripdata)\nstr(trips23)       ## See list of columns and data types (numeric, character, etc)\nsummary(trips23)   ## Statistical summary of data. Mainly for numeric.","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:22.958031Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:22.959371Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:23.327945Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**There are a few problems we will need to fix**                                                                \n   (1) The data can only be aggregated at the ride-level, which is too granular. We will want to add some additional columns of        data -- such as day, month -- that provide additional opportunities to aggregate the data.                                  \n   (2) We will want to add a calculated field for length of ride data did not have the \"tripduration\" column.                 \n                                                                        ","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## Lets see how many observations fall under each usertype\ntable(trips23$member_casual)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:23.330542Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:23.331868Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:23.747898Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"  **Adding columns that list the date, day and month of each ride the year for this dataframe gonna be for 2023                \n  This will allow us to aggregate ride data for each month, day, and day of week ... before completing these operations         \n  we could only aggregate at the ride level.                                                                      \n  [Click here](https://www.statmethods.net/input/dates.html) more on date formats in R found a that link**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"trips23<-trips23%>%\nmutate(year = format(as.Date(started_at), \"%Y\"))%>% ## 4-digit Year\nmutate(month = format(as.Date(started_at),\"%B\"))%>% ## Full month\nmutate(date = format(as.Date(started_at),\"%d\")) %>% ## Decimal date\nmutate(time = format(as.POSIXct(started_at),\"%H\"))%>%   ## for the time represented by POSIXct and Decimal %H\nmutate(day_of_week = format(as.Date(started_at),\"%A\")) ## Full weekday","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:23.750522Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:23.751868Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:30.200372Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"max(trips23$time)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:30.203724Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:30.205077Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:30.728698Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## Adding a \"ride_length\" calculation to trips23 (in seconds)\ntrips23$tripduration<-difftime(trips23$ended_at,trips23$started_at)\n##lets Inspect the structure of columns\n\n## Convert \"tripduration\" from Factor to numeric so we can run calculations on data \ntrips23$tripduration <- as.numeric(as.character(trips23$tripduration))\nis.numeric(trips23$tripduration)\nmin(trips23$tripduration)  ## shortest ride\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:30.731193Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:30.732445Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:34.623112Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Remove \"bad\" data**                                                                                                                       \n  The dataframe includes a few hundred entries when bikes were taken out of docks and checked for quality by Divvy or             tripduration was negative                                                                                                                \n  We will crate a new version of the dataframe (clean) since data is being removed\n\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"trips23_clean<-trips23[!(trips23$tripduration<0),]","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:34.62552Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:34.626788Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:34.919932Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Analyze**                                                                         \nNow we have all required information in one place and ready for exploration","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## Now lets check the cleaned data frame\nstr(trips23_clean)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:34.923903Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:34.925291Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:34.95873Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## Lets see summarised details of cleaned dataset\nsummary(trips23_clean)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:34.961193Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:34.962465Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:35.663089Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## Descriptive analysis on tripduration(allfigures in seconds)\nsummary(trips23_clean$tripduration)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:35.665504Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:35.666759Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:35.860013Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"***LETS COMPARE MEMBERS AND CASUAL USERS***","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"##Difference of members and casual riders by there total rides\ntrips23_clean %>% \n    group_by(member_casual) %>% \n    summarise(ride_count = length(rideable_type), ride_percentage = (length(rideable_type) / nrow(trips23_clean))* 100)\n\n\nggplot(trips23_clean, aes(x = member_casual, fill=member_casual)) +\n    geom_bar() +\n    labs(x=\"Casuals vs Members\", y=\"Number Of Rides\", title= \"Casuals vs Members number of rides Jan-Jul 2023\")\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:35.862512Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:35.863849Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:41.716043Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Casual riders account for approximately 37% of all rides, while Members make up the remaining 63%. Members ride approximately 26% more than Casual riders.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## Lets compare more for members and casual users  \ntrips23_clean%>%\ngroup_by(member_casual)%>%\nsummarise(min_tripduration = min(tripduration), median_tripduration = median(tripduration),\n         max_tripduration=max(tripduration),average_tripduration=mean(tripduration))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:41.718978Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:41.72041Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:41.931622Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Here we can see that the Casual riders took bikes for longer rides than Members, as on average trip duration of Members is lower then average trip duration of Casual riders**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"***LETS SEE TOTAL RIDES AND AVERAGE RIDE DURATION BY DAY OF WEEK FOR MEMBERS AND CASUAL RIDERS***","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## The days of the week are out of order. Let's fix that.\ntrips23_clean$day_of_week<-ordered(trips23_clean$day_of_week,levels=c(\"Sunday\",\"Monday\",\"Tuesday\",\"Wednesday\",\"Thursday\",\"Friday\",\"Saturday\"))\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:41.934447Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:41.935966Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:42.001327Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## Lets see the average ride duration by each day for members vs casual users\ntrips23_clean%>%\nmutate(weekday=wday(started_at,label=TRUE))%>%   ##creates weekday field using wday()\ngroup_by(member_casual,weekday)%>%       ##groups by usertype and weekday \nsummarise(number_of_rides=n(),average_duration=mean(tripduration), .groups=\"drop\")%>% ##calculates the number of rides and average duration\narrange(member_casual,weekday)             ##sorts","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:42.004308Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:42.005739Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:45.360579Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Visualize total rides by rider type and day of the week**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"trips23_clean%>%mutate(weekdays=wday(started_at,label=TRUE))%>%\ngroup_by(member_casual,weekdays)%>%\nsummarise(number_of_rides=n(),average_duration=mean(tripduration), .groups=\"drop\")%>%\narrange(member_casual,weekdays)%>%\nggplot(aes(x=weekdays,y=number_of_rides,fill=member_casual))+\nlabs(title=\"Total rides by rider type Day of the week\")+\ngeom_col(position=\"dodge\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:45.364471Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:45.366139Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:48.885381Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Lets create a visualization for average duration**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"trips23_clean%>%mutate(weekdays=wday(started_at,label=TRUE))%>%\ngroup_by(member_casual,weekdays)%>%\nsummarise(number_of_rides=n(),average_duration=mean(tripduration), .groups=\"drop\")%>%\narrange(member_casual,weekdays)%>%\nggplot(aes(x=weekdays,y=average_duration,fill=member_casual))+\nlabs(title=\"Average duration by Members and Casual riders VS Day of the week\")+\ngeom_col(position=\"dodge\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:48.888107Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:48.889445Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:52.412245Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**The first chart above shows that members traveled consistently throughout the week, but Sunday saw a decrease in trips. Weekends are typically the times of week when casual riders take the most rides, with Friday being the most popular day, followed by Saturday and Sunday.**   \n\n\n**Members typically ride for much shorter periods of time than casual riders. Additionally, the average ride length for casual riders is significantly longer on weekends, as are the total number of rides. This means that for casual riders, both of these facts are related. For members, the weekly average ride length (<1000 sec) is fairly constant.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"*****LETS SEE TOTAL RIDES AND AVERAGE RIDE DURATION BY MONTHS FOR MEMBERS AND CASUAL RIDERS*****","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## Lets fix the monts order.\ntrips23_clean$month<-ordered(trips23_clean$month,\n                             levels=c(\"January\", \"February\", \"March\", \"April\", \"May\", \"June\", \"July\", \"August\", \"September\", \"October\", \"November\", \"December\"))\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:52.41507Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:52.416448Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:52.465206Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Lets see average ride duration by rider type by months**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"trips23_clean %>%\ngroup_by(member_casual,month)%>%\nsummarise(number_of_rides = n(), average_duration=mean(tripduration),.groups=\"drop\")%>%\narrange(member_casual,month)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:52.467885Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:52.469157Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:52.594144Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Visualize total rides data by type and month**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"trips23_clean %>%  \n  group_by(member_casual, month) %>% \n  summarise(number_of_rides = n(),.groups=\"drop\") %>% \n  ggplot(aes(x = month, y = number_of_rides, fill = member_casual)) +\n  labs(title =\"Total rides by Members and Casual riders VS Month\", x = \"Month\", y= \"Number Of Rides\") +\n  geom_col(position = \"dodge\")\n  ","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:52.596765Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:52.598121Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:53.170585Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Visualize average rides data by type and month**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"trips23_clean %>%\ngroup_by(member_casual,month)%>%\nsummarise(average_tripduration=mean(tripduration),.groups=\"drop\")%>%\nggplot(aes(x=month,y=average_tripduration,fill=member_casual))+\nlabs(title=\"Average rides by Members and Casual riders on Month\",x=\"Month\",y=\"Average Trip Duration\")+\ngeom_col(position=\"dodge\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:53.173484Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:53.174891Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:53.568598Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**We can see that starting March up until July the number of rides for Members and Casual riders is growing.            \nAnd about Trip Duration we can see that its start to growing from April up until July for both riders**                           \nReminder we are working with data from January 2023 - July 2023","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"*****LETS SEE TOTAL RIDES AND AVERAGE RIDE DURATION BY HOUR IN A DAY FOR MEMBERS AND CASUAL RIDERS*****\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"##Visualize total rides data by type and hour in a day\ntrips23_clean %>%  \n  group_by(member_casual, time) %>% \n  summarise(number_of_rides = n(),.groups=\"drop\") %>%  \n  ggplot(aes(x = time, y = number_of_rides, fill = member_casual)) +\n  labs(title =\"Total rides by Members and Casual riders VS time of the day\", x = \"Time of the day\", y= \"Number Of Rides\") +\n  geom_col(position = \"dodge\")\n  ","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:53.571399Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:53.572844Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:54.243901Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"## Lets see Trip duration by Members and Casual riders VS time of the day\ntrips23_clean %>%  \n  group_by(member_casual, time) %>% \n  summarise(average_tripduration = mean(tripduration),.groups=\"drop\") %>%  \n  ggplot(aes(x = time, y = average_tripduration, fill = member_casual)) +\n  labs(title =\"Trip duration by Members and Casual riders VS time of the day\", x = \"Time of the day\", y= \"Average Trip Duration\") +\n  geom_col(position = \"dodge\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:54.248491Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:54.249897Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:54.761004Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**From above two visualizations we can tell that the volume of rides for both Members and Casual riders is growing from (05:00 - 17:00) and after 17:00 is decreasing , but the Members volume of rides is growing more then 2 times then Casuals on this (06:00 - 09:00) and (16:00 - 18:00) times of the day.\nBut on trip duration the Casual riders duration is twice longer then Members for all time of the day except from 05:00 until 08:00 there is decrease of duration time for Casual riders.**\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**ANALYSIS AND VISUALIZATION OF RIDEABLE TYPE VS TOTAL RIDES BY MEMBERS AND CASUAL RIDERS**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"trips23_clean %>%\ngroup_by(rideable_type,member_casual) %>%\nsummarise(number_of_rides=n(),.groups=\"drop\")%>%\nggplot(aes(x = rideable_type, y=number_of_rides, fill= member_casual))+\nlabs(title=\"Rideable type VS total rides by Members and Casual Ryders\",x=\"Rideable type\",y=\"Number of Rides\")+\ngeom_col(position = \"dodge\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:54.763929Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:54.765298Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:55.368961Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"trips23_clean %>%\ngroup_by(rideable_type,member_casual) %>%\nsummarise(average_tripduration = mean(tripduration),.groups=\"drop\")%>%\nggplot(aes(x = rideable_type, y=average_tripduration, fill= member_casual))+\nlabs(title=\"Rideable type VS Average trip duration by Members and Casual riders\",x=\"Rideable type\",y=\"Average Trip Duration\")+\ngeom_col(position = \"dodge\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-09-29T11:39:55.371735Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-09-29T11:39:55.373279Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-09-29T11:39:55.800289Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**From this last two visualizations we can say that the Members and Casual riders like to use more electric bikes then classic bike then the Casual riders prefer docked bikes when the Members not using it at all. \nBut at the trip duration the Casual prefer to use docket bike a lot longer then classic bikes then after electric bikes.\nWhen Members are using classic bikes little longer then electric bikes**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**The Share phase will be done by presentation, but here on Kaggle we can use Notebooks to share our analysis and visualizations**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"****Deliverable                                                                              \nA clear statement of the business task                                                                    \nFind the differences between casual and member riders.**\n\n**Ride Volume:                                                                                                                  Casual riders account for approximately 37% of all rides, while Members make up the remaining 63%. Members ride approximately 26% more than Casual riders.\nCasual riders tend to take longer rides than Members on average.**\n\n**Weekly Usage Patterns:                                                                                                    \nMembers show consistent riding patterns throughout the week, with a slight dip in rides on Sundays.\nCasual riders are more active on weekends, with Friday being the most popular day, followed by Saturday and Sunday.**\n\n**Ride Duration:                                                                                                       \nMembers typically have shorter ride durations compared to Casual riders. For Members, the weekly average ride duration remains fairly constant, typically less than 1000 seconds.\nCasual riders, on the other hand, have significantly longer rides on weekends, which correlates with higher total ride numbers during that time.**                                                                                      \n\n**Growth Trends:                                                                                                   \nBoth Members and Casual riders show a growth in the number of rides from March to July.\nTrip duration also increases from April to July for both rider types.**\n\n**Usage by Time of Day:                                                                                           \nBoth rider groups show a similar pattern of ride volume increasing from 05:00 to 17:00 and decreasing after 17:00.\nMembers have a notably larger increase in rides compared to Casual riders during the morning (06:00 - 09:00) and evening (16:00 - 18:00) periods.**                                                                                 \n\n**Bike Type Preferences:                                                                                                     \nMembers and Casual riders both prefer electric bikes over classic bikes, with Members showing a stronger preference for electric bikes.\nCasual riders tend to use docked bikes for longer durations, while Members don't use docked bikes as frequently.**\n\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"****","metadata":{}}]}